msContents.summary: Drafts of two sermons on Job 21.15, with cancellations, insertions, and Biblical references and other notes added in red ink. A contemporary paper cover bound in at the beginning of the first sermon had the title Of prayer from Job 21.15, Vth Sermon, in black ink but was changed in red ink to Sermon XCIX, Of prayer (First sermon).

supportDesc.extent: 81 leaves : 168 x 102 mm. bound to 176 x 126 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 81; [1-81]; modern pencil foliation, lower right recto, does not include guard pages between sermons.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a semi-cursive script by a single hand.

binding.p: 19th-century leather; title in gilt on upper cover, Mss. sermons of the Rt. Rev. William White.

origin.p: Probably written in Philadelphia in the last quarter of the 18th or first quarter of the 19th century.

history.provenance: Bookplate: Yarnall Library of Theology, St. Clement's Church (Philadelphia, Pa.); acquired by the Yarnall Library before 1933.
Deposited with the Yarnall Library of Theology at the University of Pennsylvania, 1974.
